                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6712: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-16T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 16, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Governor General of French Equatorial Africa reports that Free French forces
                    entered Port Gentil November 15 completing the occupation of Gabon.</p>
                <p>Businessmen, lawyers and minor Belgian Congo Government officials have formed
                    “Congo League of Patriotic Action” with a view to exerting pressure on the
                    Government to increase war effort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
